flowRoot.flowPara: This document encompasses all considerations and planning for the design of card game prototypes including popular games such as Blackjack, House Poker and Texas Hold 'em.
-Cards are dealt to any active boxes and then dealer, then the boxes receive their last starting card, leaving the dealer with one and the players with two
- All active boxes either hit until busting or sitting. Five cards or blackjacks are paid instantly.
- Dealer hits until over 16 or busted. Non busted players are paid either if their total is higher or the dealer busted
-Cards are dealt to any active boxes and then dealer leaving all with two cards including the dealer
- Active boxes are allowed to put up to x times their bet amount, allowing no further betting, or checking
- The flop is dealt, players are allowed to put x-1 times their bet amount, closing further action, or checking.
- The turn and river are dealt. Players must risk their bet amount minus the ante to win their bet amount minus the ante.
- The dealer reveals the cards and players with a better poker hand than the dealer win.
-Cards are dealt clockwise from the small blind until all players have two cards
- Starting from UTG (BUT+3), each player must fold, call or raise. If raised, players must act again before the flop is dealt
- The flop is dealt, the same course of action is taken until an amount is decided or someone elects to fold. If everyone folds, the last player wins the pot.
- The river is dealt. If players decide on an amount on this street,
all active players show their cards and a winner is decided.
The button moves clockwise and the game is played again.
AI must be capable of rating hand strength and betting sensibly. Consider programming AI in iterations, each iteration being a seperate or improved AI for difficulty levels.
Level 1: Bets soley on hand strength. Never bluffs.
Level 2: Has tweakable aggression factor and will bluff accordingly.
Level 3: Considers position and can construct hand ranges and hand read opponents.
